The overall emergency response program for the Walker Creek Gas Plant is coordinated with the Columbia County LEPC.  The Walker Creek Gas Plant has around-the-clock communications capability with appropriate LEPC officials and emergency response organizations (e.g., fire department).  This provides a means of notifying the public of an incident, if necessary, as well as facilitating quick response to an incident.

PLANNED CHANGES TO IMPROVE SAFETY

The Walker Creek Gas Plant resolves all findings from PHAs, some of which result in modifications to the process.  The following types of changes are planned over the next few years in response to the PHA, safety audit and incident investigation findings:

Installation of additional overpressure protection plant equipment;
Revisions to personnel training programs;
Revision to plant shutdown systems;
Incorporating Quantum Resource Management health and safety procedures and poilcies with current Walker Creek Gas Plant procedure and policies.
